Date: Fri, 8 Nov 2013 17:03:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 222/430] of: Clear detach flag on attach

When attaching a node always clear the detach flag. Without this change
the sequence detach, attach fails.

Signed-off-by: Pantelis Antoniou <panto@antoniou-consulting.com>
Signed-off-by: Grant Likely <grant.likely@linaro.org>
(cherry picked from commit e3963fd60a83967573f6330c9db134bd581da746)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/of/base.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/of/base.c b/drivers/of/base.c
index a0990af..0cc1ca5 100644
--- a/drivers/of/base.c
+++ b/drivers/of/base.c
@@ -1867,6 +1867,7 @@ int of_attach_node(struct device_node *np)
 	np->allnext = of_allnodes;
 	np->parent->child = np;
 	of_allnodes = np;
+	of_node_clear_flag(np, OF_DETACHED);
 	raw_spin_unlock_irqrestore(&devtree_lock, flags);
 
 	of_node_add(np);
